         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper, we solve a certain family of diophantine equations associated with a family of cyclic quartic number fields. In fact, we prove that for n ≤ 5 x 10&lt;sup&gt;6&lt;/sup&gt; and n ≥ N = 1.191 x 10&lt;sup&gt;19&lt;/sup&gt;, with n, n + 2, n&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + 4 square-free, the Thue equation Φ&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; (x, y) = x&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; - n&lt;sup&gt;2x&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sup&gt;3y&lt;/sup&gt; - (n&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; + 2n&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + 4n + 2)x&lt;sup&gt;2y&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - n&lt;sup&gt;2xy&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; + y&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; = 1 has no integral solution except the trivial ones: (1, 0), (-1, 0), (0, 1), (0, -1).</p>
          </abstract>
